{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2760,"text":"Here's a question that matters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4880,"text":"[Is it ethical to evolve the human body?]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":6880,"text":"Because we're beginning to get all\nthe tools together to evolve ourselves."},{"time":10400,"text":"And we can evolve bacteria\nand we can evolve plants"},{"time":12840,"text":"and we can evolve animals,"},{"time":14280,"text":"and we're now reaching a point\nwhere we really have to ask,"},{"time":17120,"text":"is it really ethical\nand do we want to evolve human beings?"},{"time":21440,"text":"And as you're thinking about that,"},{"time":23360,"text":"let me talk about that\nin the context of prosthetics,"},{"time":27120,"text":"prosthetics past, present, future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30920,"text":"So this is the iron hand"},{"time":32520,"text":"that belonged to one of the German counts."},{"time":34880,"text":"Loved to fight, lost his arm\nin one of these battles."},{"time":39320,"text":"No problem, he just made a suit of armor,"},{"time":41800,"text":"put it on,"},{"time":43160,"text":"perfect prosthetic."},{"time":44440,"text":"That's where the concept\nof ruling with an iron fist comes from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49600,"text":"And of course these prosthetics\nhave been getting more and more useful,"},{"time":53080,"text":"more and more modern."},{"time":54360,"text":"You can hold soft-boiled eggs."},{"time":56840,"text":"You can have all types of controls,\nand as you're thinking about that,"},{"time":60360,"text":"there are wonderful people like Hugh Herr"},{"time":62400,"text":"who have been building\nabsolutely extraordinary prosthetics."},{"time":65720,"text":"So the wonderful Aimee Mullins\nwill go out and say,"},{"time":68560,"text":"how tall do I want to be tonight?"},{"time":71040,"text":"Or Hugh will say what type of cliff\ndo I want to climb?"},{"time":73960,"text":"Or does somebody want to run a marathon,\nor does somebody want to ballroom dance?"},{"time":78480,"text":"And as you adapt these things,"},{"time":80480,"text":"the interesting thing about prosthetics\nis they've been coming inside the body."},{"time":84640,"text":"So these external prosthetics\nhave now become artificial knees."},{"time":87640,"text":"They've become artificial hips."},{"time":89720,"text":"And then they've evolved further"},{"time":91960,"text":"to become not just nice to have"},{"time":94000,"text":"but essential to have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95920,"text":"So when you're talking\nabout a heart pacemaker as a prosthetic,"},{"time":99800,"text":"you're talking about something\nthat isn't just, \"I'm missing my leg,\""},{"time":103520,"text":"it's, \"if I don't have this, I can die.\""},{"time":105960,"text":"And at that point, a prosthetic\nbecomes a symbiotic relationship"},{"time":110080,"text":"with the human body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112560,"text":"And four of the smartest people\nthat I've ever met --"},{"time":115120,"text":"Ed Boyden, Hugh Herr,\nJoe Jacobson, Bob Lander --"},{"time":120400,"text":"are working on a Center\nfor Extreme Bionics."},{"time":123000,"text":"And the interesting thing\nof what you're seeing here is"},{"time":125640,"text":"these prosthetics\nnow get integrated into the bone."},{"time":128080,"text":"They get integrated into the skin."},{"time":129759,"text":"They get integrated into the muscle."},{"time":132360,"text":"And one of the other sides of Ed"},{"time":135360,"text":"is he's been thinking\nabout how to connect the brain"},{"time":138280,"text":"using light or other mechanisms"},{"time":141000,"text":"directly to things like these prosthetics."},{"time":144520,"text":"And if you can do that,"},{"time":145800,"text":"then you can begin changing\nfundamental aspects of humanity."},{"time":149840,"text":"So how quickly you react to something\ndepends on the diameter of a nerve."},{"time":154920,"text":"And of course, if you have nerves\nthat are external or prosthetic,"},{"time":159600,"text":"say with light or liquid metal,"},{"time":162280,"text":"then you can increase that diameter"},{"time":164000,"text":"and you could even increase it\ntheoretically to the point where,"},{"time":167080,"text":"as long as you could see the muzzle flash,\nyou could step out of the way of a bullet."},{"time":171840,"text":"Those are the order of magnitude\nof changes you're talking about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176200,"text":"This is a fourth\nsort of level of prosthetics."},{"time":178800,"text":"These are Phonak hearing aids,"},{"time":181360,"text":"and the reason\nwhy these are so interesting"},{"time":183440,"text":"is because they cross the threshold\nfrom where prosthetics are something"},{"time":186880,"text":"for somebody who is \"disabled\""},{"time":189560,"text":"and they become something\nthat somebody who is \"normal\""},{"time":193640,"text":"might want to actually have,"},{"time":195560,"text":"because what this prosthetic does,\nwhich is really interesting,"},{"time":198560,"text":"is not only does it help you hear,"},{"time":200240,"text":"you can focus your hearing,"},{"time":201600,"text":"so it can hear the conversation\ngoing on over there."},{"time":204080,"text":"You can have superhearing."},{"time":205360,"text":"You can have hearing in 360 degrees.\nYou can have white noise."},{"time":208320,"text":"You can record, and oh, by the way,\nthey also put a phone into this."},{"time":212440,"text":"So this functions as your hearing aid\nand also as your phone."},{"time":215920,"text":"And at that point, somebody might actually\nwant to have a prosthetic voluntarily."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222400,"text":"All of these thousands\nof loosely connected little pieces"},{"time":225120,"text":"are coming together,"},{"time":227120,"text":"and it's about time we ask the question,"},{"time":229080,"text":"how do we want to evolve human beings\nover the next century or two?"},{"time":233640,"text":"And for that we turn\nto a great philosopher"},{"time":236920,"text":"who was a very smart man\ndespite being a Yankee fan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":242800,"text":"And Yogi Berra used to say, of course,\nthat it's very tough to make predictions,"},{"time":246640,"text":"especially about the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248040,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":249160,"text":"So instead of making a prediction\nabout the future to begin with,"},{"time":252240,"text":"let's take what's happening in the present\nwith people like Tony Atala,"},{"time":255600,"text":"who is redesigning 30-some-odd organs."},{"time":259200,"text":"And maybe the ultimate prosthetic\nisn't having something external, titanium."},{"time":262800,"text":"Maybe the ultimate prosthetic\nis take your own gene code,"},{"time":265520,"text":"remake your own body parts,"},{"time":267920,"text":"because that's a whole lot more effective\nthan any kind of a prosthetic."},{"time":272440,"text":"But while you're at it, then you can take\nthe work of Craig Venter and Ham Smith."},{"time":276480,"text":"And one of the things\nthat we've been doing"},{"time":278560,"text":"is trying to figure out\nhow to reprogram cells."},{"time":282280,"text":"And if you can reprogram a cell,"},{"time":283880,"text":"then you can change the cells\nin those organs."},{"time":287400,"text":"So if you can change\nthe cells in those organs,"},{"time":289640,"text":"maybe you make those organs\nmore radiation-resistant."},{"time":292160,"text":"Maybe you make them absorb more oxygen."},{"time":294080,"text":"Maybe you make them more efficient"},{"time":295760,"text":"to filter out stuff\nthat you don't want in your body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299440,"text":"And over the last few weeks,\nGeorge Church has been in the news a lot"},{"time":303120,"text":"because he's been talking about taking\none of these programmable cells"},{"time":306440,"text":"and inserting an entire human genome"},{"time":308200,"text":"into that cell."},{"time":310480,"text":"And once you can insert\nan entire human genome into a cell,"},{"time":314320,"text":"then you begin to ask the question,"},{"time":316480,"text":"would you want\nto enhance any of that genome?"},{"time":321440,"text":"Do you want to enhance a human body?"},{"time":323800,"text":"How would you want\nto enhance a human body?"},{"time":326120,"text":"Where is it ethical\nto enhance a human body"},{"time":328240,"text":"and where is it not ethical\nto enhance a human body?"},{"time":331520,"text":"And all of a sudden, what we're doing"},{"time":333440,"text":"is we've got this\nmultidimensional chess board"},{"time":336400,"text":"where we can change\nhuman genetics by using viruses"},{"time":339680,"text":"to attack things like AIDS,"},{"time":342120,"text":"or we can change the gene code\nthrough gene therapy"},{"time":344560,"text":"to do away with some hereditary diseases,"},{"time":347520,"text":"or we can change the environment,"},{"time":349160,"text":"and change the expression\nof those genes in the epigenome"},{"time":351851,"text":"and pass that on to the next generations."},{"time":355320,"text":"And all of a sudden,\nit's not just one little bit,"},{"time":358480,"text":"it's all these stacked little bits"},{"time":360360,"text":"that allow you\nto take little portions of it"},{"time":363280,"text":"until all the portions coming together"},{"time":366160,"text":"lead you to something\nthat's very different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369600,"text":"And a lot of people\nare very scared by this stuff."},{"time":372360,"text":"And it does sound scary,\nand there are risks to this stuff."},{"time":376040,"text":"So why in the world would you\never want to do this stuff?"},{"time":378760,"text":"Why would we really want\nto alter the human body"},{"time":381800,"text":"in a fundamental way?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":385040,"text":"The answer lies in part"},{"time":387360,"text":"with Lord Rees,"},{"time":389240,"text":"astronomer royal of Great Britain."},{"time":392560,"text":"And one of his favorite sayings\nis the universe is 100 percent malevolent."},{"time":396400,"text":"So what does that mean?"},{"time":397640,"text":"It means if you take\nany one of your bodies at random,"},{"time":400560,"text":"drop it anywhere in the universe,"},{"time":402480,"text":"drop it in space, you die."},{"time":404720,"text":"Drop it on the Sun, you die."},{"time":406120,"text":"Drop it on the surface\nof Mercury, you die."},{"time":408160,"text":"Drop it near a supernova, you die."},{"time":410240,"text":"But fortunately, it's only\nabout 80 percent effective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414640,"text":"So as a great physicist once said,"},{"time":418000,"text":"there's these little\nupstream eddies of biology"},{"time":422160,"text":"that create order\nin this rapid torrent of entropy."},{"time":428080,"text":"So as the universe dissipates energy,"},{"time":431080,"text":"there's these upstream eddies\nthat create biological order."},{"time":435960,"text":"Now, the problem with eddies is,"},{"time":438400,"text":"they tend to disappear."},{"time":439920,"text":"They shift. They move in rivers."},{"time":442680,"text":"And because of that, when an eddy shifts,"},{"time":444680,"text":"when the Earth becomes a snowball,\nwhen the Earth becomes very hot,"},{"time":448240,"text":"when the Earth gets hit by an asteroid,\nwhen you have supervolcanoes,"},{"time":451520,"text":"when you have solar flares,"},{"time":453400,"text":"when you have potentially\nextinction-level events"},{"time":456760,"text":"like the next election --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":458000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":461440,"text":"then all of a sudden,\nyou can have periodic extinctions."},{"time":465400,"text":"And by the way, that's happened\nfive times on Earth,"},{"time":468360,"text":"and therefore it is very likely"},{"time":470480,"text":"that the human species on Earth\nis going to go extinct someday."},{"time":474440,"text":"Not next week,"},{"time":475960,"text":"not next month,"},{"time":477800,"text":"maybe in November,\nbut maybe 10,000 years after that."},{"time":481880,"text":"As you're thinking\nof the consequence of that,"},{"time":484720,"text":"if you believe that extinctions\nare common and natural"},{"time":488160,"text":"and normal and occur periodically,"},{"time":490480,"text":"it becomes a moral imperative\nto diversify our species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494520,"text":"And it becomes a moral imperative"},{"time":496160,"text":"because it's going to be\nreally hard to live on Mars"},{"time":499160,"text":"if we don't fundamentally\nmodify the human body."},{"time":502880,"text":"Right?"},{"time":504120,"text":"You go from one cell,"},{"time":505480,"text":"mom and dad coming together\nto make one cell,"},{"time":507720,"text":"in a cascade to 10 trillion cells."},{"time":509920,"text":"We don't know, if you change\nthe gravity substantially,"},{"time":514400,"text":"if the same thing will happen\nto create your body."},{"time":518159,"text":"We do know that if you expose\nour bodies as they currently are"},{"time":521240,"text":"to a lot of radiation, we will die."},{"time":525040,"text":"So as you're thinking of that,\nyou have to really redesign things"},{"time":528120,"text":"just to get to Mars."},{"time":529400,"text":"Forget about the moons\nof Neptune or Jupiter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533000,"text":"And to borrow from Nikolai Kardashev,"},{"time":535480,"text":"let's think about life\nin a series of scales."},{"time":537680,"text":"So Life One civilization"},{"time":540200,"text":"is a civilization that begins\nto alter his or her looks."},{"time":544080,"text":"And we've been doing that\nfor thousands of years."},{"time":546400,"text":"You've got tummy tucks\nand you've got this and you've got that."},{"time":550280,"text":"You alter your looks, and I'm told"},{"time":552720,"text":"that not all of those alterations\ntake place for medical reasons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":558760,"text":"Seems odd."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560360,"text":"A Life Two civilization\nis a different civilization."},{"time":564320,"text":"A Life Two civilization alters\nfundamental aspects of the body."},{"time":569840,"text":"So you put human growth hormone in,\nthe person grows taller,"},{"time":572720,"text":"or you put x in and the person\ngets fatter or loses metabolism"},{"time":576680,"text":"or does a whole series of things,"},{"time":578320,"text":"but you're altering the functions\nin a fundamental way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581040,"text":"To become an intrasolar civilization,"},{"time":583680,"text":"we're going to have to create\na Life Three civilization,"},{"time":587720,"text":"and that looks very different\nfrom what we've got here."},{"time":590840,"text":"Maybe you splice in\nDeinococcus radiodurans"},{"time":593080,"text":"so that the cells can resplice\nafter a lot of exposure to radiation."},{"time":598320,"text":"Maybe you breathe by having oxygen\nflow through your blood"},{"time":601360,"text":"instead of through your lungs."},{"time":603600,"text":"But you're talking about\nreally radical redesigns,"},{"time":607480,"text":"and one of the interesting things\nthat's happened in the last decade"},{"time":610720,"text":"is we've discovered\na whole lot of planets out there."},{"time":613480,"text":"And some of them may be Earth-like."},{"time":617440,"text":"The problem is, if we ever\nwant to get to these planets,"},{"time":621080,"text":"the fastest human objects --"},{"time":622760,"text":"Juno and Voyager\nand the rest of this stuff --"},{"time":625360,"text":"take tens of thousands of years"},{"time":627880,"text":"to get from here\nto the nearest solar system."},{"time":630720,"text":"So if you want to start exploring\nbeaches somewhere else,"},{"time":634400,"text":"or you want to see two-sun sunsets,"},{"time":637840,"text":"then you're talking\nabout something that is very different,"},{"time":641000,"text":"because you have to change\nthe timescale and the body of humans"},{"time":646080,"text":"in ways which may be\nabsolutely unrecognizable."},{"time":650000,"text":"And that's a Life Four civilization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653720,"text":"Now, we can't even begin\nto imagine what that might look like,"},{"time":656680,"text":"but we're beginning to get glimpses"},{"time":659040,"text":"of instruments that might\ntake us even that far."},{"time":662960,"text":"And let me give you two examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664600,"text":"So this is the wonderful Floyd Romesberg,"},{"time":667200,"text":"and one of the things\nthat Floyd's been doing"},{"time":669360,"text":"is he's been playing\nwith the basic chemistry of life."},{"time":671920,"text":"So all life on this planet\nis made in ATCGs, the four letters of DNA."},{"time":676800,"text":"All bacteria, all plants,\nall animals, all humans, all cows,"},{"time":679960,"text":"everything else."},{"time":682440,"text":"And what Floyd did is he changed out\ntwo of those base pairs,"},{"time":686640,"text":"so it's ATXY."},{"time":689760,"text":"And that means that you now have\na parallel system to make life,"},{"time":695480,"text":"to make babies, to reproduce, to evolve,"},{"time":699800,"text":"that doesn't mate\nwith most things on Earth"},{"time":702000,"text":"or in fact maybe with nothing on Earth."},{"time":704880,"text":"Maybe you make plants\nthat are immune to all bacteria."},{"time":707440,"text":"Maybe you make plants\nthat are immune to all viruses."},{"time":709960,"text":"But why is that so interesting?"},{"time":711520,"text":"It means that we\nare not a unique solution."},{"time":715400,"text":"It means you can create\nalternate chemistries to us"},{"time":719160,"text":"that could be chemistries\nadaptable to a very different planet"},{"time":724000,"text":"that could create life and heredity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728120,"text":"The second experiment,"},{"time":730480,"text":"or the other implication\nof this experiment,"},{"time":733360,"text":"is that all of you, all life\nis based on 20 amino acids."},{"time":737600,"text":"If you don't substitute two amino acids,"},{"time":740080,"text":"if you don't say ATXY,\nif you say ATCG + XY,"},{"time":745680,"text":"then you go from\n20 building blocks to 172,"},{"time":749520,"text":"and all of a sudden you've got\n172 building blocks of amino acids"},{"time":752680,"text":"to build life-forms\nin very different shapes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757480,"text":"The second experiment to think about\nis a really weird experiment"},{"time":760560,"text":"that's been taking place in China."},{"time":763920,"text":"So this guy has been transplanting\nhundreds of mouse heads."},{"time":768920,"text":"Right?"},{"time":770320,"text":"And why is that an interesting experiment?"},{"time":773440,"text":"Well, think of the first\nheart transplants."},{"time":775520,"text":"One of the things they used to do"},{"time":777160,"text":"is they used to bring in\nthe wife or the daughter of the donor"},{"time":780720,"text":"so the donee could tell the doctors,"},{"time":784640,"text":"\"Do you recognize this person?\nDo you love this person?"},{"time":787280,"text":"Do you feel anything for this person?\""},{"time":789160,"text":"We laugh about that today."},{"time":791560,"text":"We laugh because we know\nthe heart is a muscle,"},{"time":793800,"text":"but for hundreds of thousands of years,\nor tens of thousands of years,"},{"time":797320,"text":"\"I gave her my heart.\nShe took my heart. She broke my heart.\""},{"time":800240,"text":"We thought this was emotion"},{"time":801640,"text":"and we thought maybe emotions\nwere transplanted with the heart. Nope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"So how about the brain?"},{"time":809040,"text":"Two possible outcomes to this experiment."},{"time":811880,"text":"If you can get a mouse"},{"time":814320,"text":"that is functional,"},{"time":815960,"text":"then you can see,"},{"time":818040,"text":"is the new brain a blank slate?"},{"time":821280,"text":"And boy, does that have implications."},{"time":825120,"text":"Second option:"},{"time":826800,"text":"the new mouse recognizes Minnie Mouse."},{"time":829760,"text":"The new mouse\nremembers what it's afraid of,"},{"time":831880,"text":"remembers how to navigate the maze,"},{"time":833600,"text":"and if that is true,"},{"time":836040,"text":"then you can transplant\nmemory and consciousness."},{"time":841080,"text":"And then the really\ninteresting question is,"},{"time":843520,"text":"if you can transplant this,\nis the only input-output mechanism"},{"time":847480,"text":"this down here?"},{"time":849440,"text":"Or could you transplant\nthat consciousness into something"},{"time":852160,"text":"that would be very different,"},{"time":854160,"text":"that would last in space,"},{"time":855440,"text":"that would last\ntens of thousands of years,"},{"time":857520,"text":"that would be a completely redesigned body"},{"time":859544,"text":"that could hold consciousness\nfor a long, long period of time?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":866040,"text":"And let's come back to the first question:"},{"time":868560,"text":"Why would you ever want to do that?"},{"time":872320,"text":"Well, I'll tell you why."},{"time":873600,"text":"Because this is the ultimate selfie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":878440,"text":"This is taken from six billion miles away,"},{"time":882040,"text":"and that's Earth."},{"time":884800,"text":"And that's all of us."},{"time":887240,"text":"And if that little thing goes,\nall of humanity goes."},{"time":892320,"text":"And the reason you want\nto alter the human body"},{"time":894560,"text":"is because you eventually\nwant a picture that says,"},{"time":897360,"text":"that's us, and that's us,"},{"time":899320,"text":"and that's us,"},{"time":900760,"text":"because that's the way humanity\nsurvives long-term extinction."},{"time":905440,"text":"And that's the reason why it turns out"},{"time":907720,"text":"it's actually unethical\nnot to evolve the human body"},{"time":911680,"text":"even though it can be scary,\neven though it can be challenging,"},{"time":915040,"text":"but it's what's going\nto allow us to explore, live"},{"time":918440,"text":"and get to places\nwe can't even dream of today,"},{"time":921760,"text":"but which our great-great-great-great-\ngrandchildren might someday."}]},{"cues":[{"time":925520,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":926760,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}